il and obtain upper bounds in $\\mathcal{O}\\left(M\\log\nM\\right)$, where the constants depend only linearly on the spatial dimension.\nWith high probability, we construct spatial discretizations where $M/T\\le C\\log\nT$ holds, which implies that the complexity of the corresponding FFT converts\nto $\\mathcal{O}\\left(T\\log^2 T\\right)$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 21 Mar 2017 14:06:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 17 Nov 2017 16:06:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-20"}
